################ DESCRIPTION ###############

Example for generating and running a simulation with the All-atom model using SMOG 3 and OpenSMOG.

############### PREREQUISITES ##############

- SMOG 3 must be installed (`pip install .`)
- Java (for contact map generation)
- OpenSMOG (for running the simulation, optional for this generation step)

######### USING SMOG 3 #######

Begin with the file 2ci2.pdb.

1. Preprocess the PDB file.
   If you have the legacy `smog_adjustPDB` tool, you can use it.
   Otherwise, ensure your PDB is clean (no water, standard naming).

   (Assuming clean PDB for this example)
   `cp 2ci2.pdb 2ci2.adjusted.pdb`

2. Generate your force field with smog3:
   - The -AA flag indicates that the Whitford '09 all-atom model should be used.

   > smog3 -i 2ci2.adjusted.pdb -AA -dname 2ci2.OpenSMOG.AA

   Note: SMOG 3 generates GROMACS-compatible files by default which are also compatible with OpenSMOG.

#### RUNNING A SIMULATION WITH OPENSMOG ####

At this point, you have all files needed to start your calculations in OpenSMOG.
Use the provided script `run.ci2.OpenSMOG.AA.py` (placeholder) to run the simulation.

> python run.ci2.OpenSMOG.AA.py
